options: ['am', 'is', 'are', 'clever', 'a', 'girl', 'Mary'],\n        answer: 'Mary is a clever girl',\n      },\n    ]\"\n/>\n\n### 3. be åŠ¨è¯çš„ç¼©ç•¥å½¢å¼\n\n- am å¸¸ç¼©ç•¥ä¸º 'm ï¼ˆå¦‚ I am = I'mï¼‰\n- is å¸¸ç¼©ç•¥ä¸º's ï¼ˆå¦‚ He is = He'sï¼‰\n- are å¸¸ç¼©ç•¥ä¸º 're ï¼ˆå¦‚ You are = You'reï¼‰\n\n::: tip ç†Ÿè¯»\n\nä»¥ä¸‹ç»„åˆéå¸¸å¸¸ç”¨ï¼Œä¸ç®¡æ˜¯å®Œæ•´å½¢å¼ï¼Œè¿˜æ˜¯ç¼©å†™ï¼Œéƒ½å»ºè®®ç†Ÿè¯»ï¼Œæé«˜é€ å¥ååº”é€Ÿåº¦ï¼š\n\n::: collapse\n\n- ç‚¹å‡»å±•å¼€\n  - I am = I'm\n  - You are = You're\n  - He is = He's\n  - She is = She's\n  - It is = It's\n  - We are = We're\n  - They are = They're\n  - This is\n  - That is = That's\n\n:::\n\n### 4. å« be åŠ¨è¯çš„å¦å®šå¥\n\nè‹±è¯­è¡¨ç¤ºå¦å®šä¸€èˆ¬==åŠ  not==ã€‚åœ¨å«æœ‰ be åŠ¨è¯çš„å¥å­ä¸­ï¼Œ==ä¸€èˆ¬åŠ åœ¨ be åŠ¨è¯åé¢==ã€‚not å¸¸ç¼©ç•¥ä¸º n'tã€‚\n\n- I am a student. æˆ‘æ˜¯ä¸€åå­¦ç”Ÿã€‚\n- I ==am not== a student. æˆ‘==ä¸æ˜¯==ä¸€åå­¦ç”Ÿã€‚\n\n| é™ˆè¿° | å¦å®š    | å¦å®šç¼©ç•¥å½¢å¼ |\n| ---- | ------- | ------------ |\n| am   | am not  | æ—            |\n| are  | are not | aren't       |\n| is   | is not  | isn't        |\n\n<MakeSentence\n:questions=\"[\n    {\n      stem: 'ä»–ä¸æ˜¯æˆ‘çš„æœ‹å‹',\n      options: ['am', 'is', 'are', 'my', 'not', 'friend', 'He'],\n      answer: 'He is not my friend',\n    },\n    {\n      stem: 'è¿™ä¸æ˜¯å¥¹çš„ä¹¦ã€‚',\n      options: ['am', 'is', 'are', 'her', 'This', 'not', 'book'],\n      answer: 'This is not her book',\n    },\n    {\n      stem: 'æˆ‘å¦ˆå¦ˆä¸åœ¨å®¶ã€‚',\n      options: ['am not', 'isn\\'t', 'aren\\'t', 'My', 'home', 'mother', 'at', 'home'],\n      answer: 'My mother isn\\'t at home',\n    },\n    {\n      stem: 'ä»Šå¤©å¤©æ°”ä¸å¥½ã€‚',\n      options: ['am not', 'isn\\'t', 'aren\\'t', 'weather', 'nice today', 'The'],\n      answer: ['The', 'weather', 'isn\\'t', 'nice today'] ,\n    },\n    {\n      stem: 'é‚£åªçŒ«ä¸èƒ–ã€‚',\n      options: ['am', 'is', 'are', 'That', 'fat', 'cat', 'not'],\n      answer: 'That cat is not fat',\n    },\n    {\n      stem: 'ä»–ä»¬ä¸åœ¨æ•™å®¤é‡Œã€‚',\n      options: ['am', 'is', 'are', 'the', 'They', 'in', 'classroom', 'not'],\n      answer: 'They are not in the classroom',\n    },\n]\"\n/>\n\n### 5. å« be åŠ¨è¯çš„ä¸€èˆ¬ç–‘é—®å¥\n\nä¸€èˆ¬ç–‘é—®å¥ï¼Œæ˜¯éœ€è¦ç”¨ Yes/No å›ç­”çš„é—®å¥ã€‚ä¸€èˆ¬æ˜¯åœ¨é™ˆè¿°å¥çš„åŸºç¡€ä¸Šï¼Œå°† be åŠ¨è¯æå‰åˆ°å¥é¦–ã€‚\n\n- You ==are== happy. --> ==Are== you happy? ä½ å¼€å¿ƒå—ï¼Ÿ\n- He ==is== tall. --> ==Is== he tall? ä»–é«˜å—ï¼Ÿ\n- Your parents ==are== at home. --> ==Are== your parents at home? ä½ çš„çˆ¶æ¯åœ¨å®¶å—ï¼Ÿ\n\n<MakeSentence\n:questions=\"[\n    {\n      stem: 'ä»–æ˜¯ä½ çš„å“¥å“¥å—ï¼Ÿ',\n      options: ['Is','brother', 'your', 'he'],\n      answer: 'Is he your brother',\n    },\n    {\n      stem: 'ä½ ä»¬æ˜¯å­¦ç”Ÿå—ï¼Ÿ',\n      options: ['Are', 'students', 'you'],\n      answer: 'Are you students',\n    },\n    {\n      stem: 'Tomçš„ç‹—æ˜¯ç™½è‰²çš„å—ï¼Ÿ',\n      options: ['Tom\\'s', 'white', 'dog', 'Is'],\n      answer: 'Is Tom\\'s dog white',\n    },\n    {\n      stem: 'ä»Šå¤©çš„ä½œä¸šéš¾å—ï¼Ÿ',\n      options: ['Am', 'Is', 'Are', 'homework', 'today\\'s', 'difficult'],\n      answer: 'Is today\\'s homework difficult',\n    },\n    {\n      stem: 'è¿™æ˜¯ä½ çš„ç¬”å—ï¼ŸğŸ–Š',\n      options: ['Am', 'Is', 'Are', 'pen', 'this', 'your'],\n      answer: 'Is this your pen',\n    },\n    {\n      stem: 'ä»–ä»¬åœ¨æ•™å®¤é‡Œå—ã€‚',\n      options: ['Am', 'Is', 'Are', 'the', 'they', 'in', 'classroom'],\n      answer: 'Are they in the classroom',\n    },\n]\"\n/>\n\nå« be åŠ¨è¯çš„ä¸€èˆ¬ç–‘é—®å¥ï¼Œå›ç­”æ–¹å¼å¦‚ä¸‹ï¼š\n\n- ==è‚¯å®šå›ç­”ï¼šYes, + ä¸»è¯­ + be åŠ¨è¯==\n  - Yes, I am.\n  - Yes, he is.\n  - Yes, they are.\n- ==å¦å®šå›ç­”ï¼šNo, + ä¸»è¯­ + be åŠ¨è¯ + not==\n  - No, I am not.\n  - No, he is not. = No, he isn't.\n  - No, they are not. = No, they aren't.\n\n::: tip ç†Ÿè¯»\n\nä»¥ä¸‹ç»„åˆéå¸¸å¸¸ç”¨ï¼Œå»ºè®®ç†Ÿè¯»ï¼Œæé«˜é€ å¥é€Ÿåº¦ï¼š\n\n::: collapse\n\n- å¸¸å‡ºç°åœ¨é—®å¥å¼€å¤´ï¼š\n\n  - Are you, Are they, Are we\n  - Is he, Is she, Is it\n  - Is this, Is that\n\n- å¸¸ç”¨äºå›ç­”ï¼š\n\n  - Yes, I am. / No, I am not.\n  - Yes, you are. / No, you aren't.\n  - Yes, he is. / No, he isn't.\n  - Yes, she is. / No, she isn't.\n  - Yes, it is. / No, it isn't.\n  - Yes, we are. / No, we aren't.\n  - Yes, they are. / No, they aren't.\n\n:::\n\n### 4. å« be åŠ¨è¯çš„ç‰¹æ®Šç–‘é—®å¥ â­â­â­\n\nè¯¢é—®å…·ä½“äº‹ç‰©æˆ–æƒ…å†µæ—¶ï¼Œç”¨ç‰¹æ®Šç–‘é—®å¥ï¼Œç”±ç‰¹æ®Šç–‘é—®è¯å¼€å¤´ã€‚\n\nå« be åŠ¨è¯çš„ç‰¹æ®Šç–‘é—®å¥å¥å‹ä¸ºï¼šç‰¹æ®Šç–‘é—®è¯ + be åŠ¨è¯ + ä¸»è¯­ + å…¶ä»–\n\n<QuestionContainer\n  :questionList=\"[\n    {\n      stem: 'ä½ å‡ å²äº†ï¼Ÿ',\n      options: ['are', 'how old', 'you', 'is', 'am'],\n      answer: ['how old', 'are', 'you'],\n      sentence: 'How old are you?',\n    },\n    {\n      stem: 'Mikeåœ¨å“ªï¼Ÿ',\n      options: ['are','is', 'am', 'where',  'Mike'],\n      answer: ['where', 'is', 'Mike'],\n      sentence: 'Where is Mike?',\n    },\n    {\n      stem: 'ä½ å¥½å—ï¼Ÿ',\n      options: ['are','is', 'am', 'how', 'you'],\n      answer: ['how', 'are', 'you'],\n      sentence: 'How are you?',\n    },\n    {\n      stem: 'ä½ çš„åŒ…æ˜¯ä»€ä¹ˆé¢œè‰²çš„ï¼Ÿ',\n      options: ['are','is', 'am','color', 'bag', 'what', 'your'],\n      answer: ['what', 'color', 'is', 'your', 'bag'],\n      sentence: 'What color is your bag?',\n    },\n  ]\"\n/>\n\n::: tip ç†Ÿè¯»\n\nä»¥ä¸‹ç»„åˆéå¸¸å¸¸ç”¨ï¼Œå»ºè®®ç†Ÿè¯»ï¼Œæé«˜é€ å¥é€Ÿåº¦ï¼š\n\n- What is, What are\n- How is, How are\n- Who is, Who are\n\n:::\n\n## ç»¼åˆç»ƒä¹ \n\n<FillIn\n:questions=\"[\n{\nstem: ['â€”{{1}} you Jack\\'s friend? ','â€”No, I {{2}} his brother. (be)'],\nanswer: ['Are','am'],\nexplanation: 'å¥æ„ï¼šä½ æ˜¯ Jack çš„æœ‹å‹å—ï¼Ÿ ä¸ï¼Œæˆ‘æ˜¯ä»–çš„å“¥å“¥ã€‚é—®å¥ä¸»è¯­æ˜¯ youï¼Œbe åŠ¨è¯ç”¨ areï¼›ç­”å¥ä¸»è¯­æ˜¯ Iï¼Œbe åŠ¨è¯ç”¨ amã€‚'\n},\n{\nstem: 'This {{1}} (not be) my pen.',\nanswer: ['isn\\'t'],\nexplanation: 'å¥æ„ï¼šè¿™ä¸æ˜¯æˆ‘çš„ç¬”ã€‚æŒ‡ç¤ºä»£è¯ This ä½œä¸»è¯­ï¼Œå•æ•°ï¼Œbe åŠ¨è¯ç”¨ isã€‚åŒæ—¶ is çš„å¦å®šå½¢å¼ä¸º is notï¼Œç¼©ç•¥å½¢å¼ä¸º isn\\'tã€‚æ¯ç©ºä¸€è¯ï¼Œæ•…å¡« isn\\'tã€‚',\n},\n{\nstem: 'My phone number {{1}} 